The paper proposes a model for saliency estimation and eye fixation prediction using both bottom-up and top-down cues. The model involves deep neural networks and feature learning, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the integration of the two pathways using maxima normalization, which is a technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of adaptive sparse representation and information maximization, which are techniques commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE).
